# yt-dlp Migration Plan (Agent Teams)

## Overview

This document outlines the migration from `@distube/ytdl-core` (archived and broken) to `yt-dlp` for YouTube audio streaming in the Discord Music Bot. The plan is organized into phases suitable for parallel agent team execution.

## Why Migrate?

The current `@distube/ytdl-core` library:
- Was **archived on August 16, 2025** and receives no updates
- Cannot parse YouTube's current signature cipher algorithms
- Returns 403 Forbidden errors when attempting to stream audio
- Will never be fixed

---

## Phase Overview

| Phase | Team | Description | Dependencies | Parallelizable |
|-------|------|-------------|--------------|----------------|
| 0 | Infra | Prerequisites & environment setup | None | No |
| 1 | Dependencies | Update package.json | Phase 0 | Yes |
| 2A | Core | Implement youtube.js core functions | Phase 1 | Yes |
| 2B | Core | Implement youtube.js streaming | Phase 1 | Yes (with 2A) |
| 2C | Core | Implement youtube.js playlist support | Phase 1 | Yes (with 2A) |
| 3 | Integration | Update player.js integration | Phase 2A, 2B | No |
| 4 | Config | Environment configuration | Phase 1 | Yes (with Phase 2) |
| 5 | QA | Testing & validation | Phase 3 | No |
| 6 | Docs | Documentation & cleanup | Phase 5 | No |

